20. Qa4 Rfd8 $11 {Wojtaszek - Ding Liren, Khanty-Mansiysk, 2017}) 18... Nxe4
19. Bxe4 h6 20. Qc3 Be6 $11 {Matlakov - Motylev, Yekaterinburg, 2013}) 16... h6
17. Nxf6+ Qxf6 18. e4 (18. exd4 Qxd4 19. Rad1 Qb6 $11) {and here the timely
transfer} 18... Bd7 19. f4 Bb5 $1 {seems to be the ultimate equalizer, e.g.}
20. Bxb5 axb5 21. e5 Qe6 $11) (10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Bd2 (12. h3 Be6)
12... Re8 13. h3 Be6 $11) 10... dxe4 {Now all the central pawns will disappear
