11. Ra1 Bb4+ 12. Bd2 Bxd2+ 13. Qxd2 Ne4 14. Qb4 (14. Qe3 Qd6 $19 {[%cal Gd6b4]
, it is worth mentioning that the same move is expected in reply to 14.Qf4, by
which Black ignores the threat against the f7-pawn and almost forces the
opponent to 15.Nd3 exd3 16.Qxd6 Nxd6 17.e3 Bd3 with chances to resist.}) ({
The same imminent queen check turns into a nightmare for White after} 14. Qd1
