16. Kd1 Qd4+ 17. Ke1 Qxe5 18. fxe4 Nc6 19. Qc3 Qxe4 20. Qxg7 Rf8 $19) 7... Bb7
8. Bg2 h6 {A proper moment to question this bishop.} 9. Bf4 ({an evident
concession is} 9. Bxf6 gxf6 10. Nf3 Nd7 $17) 9... Nd5 $15) ({Gambit ideas after
} 6. g3 $6 {have been the subject of Chapter 4, here 5.Bg5 is badly
correlating to this plan -} b5 7. Bg2 Bb7 {and now:} 8. O-O (8. a4 a6 {will
inevitably transpose to one of the lines below}) (8. Bxf6 {is instructively
answered with} gxf6 $1 9. O-O Nd7 10. a4 $140 a6 11. Nd2 (11. e3 Qc7) 11... Qc8
$132 (11... Rb8 $5)) 8... Nbd7 9. a4 (9. Ne5 $6 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Qxd1 11. Rfxd1
Nd5 12. a4 b4 13. Ne4 h6 $15) 9... a6 10. Ne5 Qc8 11. Nxd7 Nxd7 12. e4 b4 13.
Nb1 a5 14. Re1 ({the logical} 14. Nd2 {has already been tested, Black has not
experienced difficulties after} c3 15. bxc3 bxc3 16. Nb1 Ba6 17. Re1 Bb4 18.
Qc2 e5 19. Be3 O-O 20. Nxc3 Nb6 $15 {[%cal Gb6c4] Wettstein - Lebled, ICCF
email, 2018}) ({less precise is} 14. Qc2 c5 (14... Ba6) 15. d5 Bd6 ({worth
