bxc3 ({the best practical try seems to be} 19. Nc4 cxb2 20. Rab1 {, when only
a thorough analysis can determine whether Black is staying on top after} Qc7)
19... Bxc3 {and here} 20. Nc4 {is not that powerful in the view of} O-O 21. Nd6
Qc6 $15) 14... c5 (14... h6) 15. d5 {and here Black can opt for the same} c3 $5
({a sound alternative is} 15... Ne5) 16. bxc3 c4 $132) 6... b5 $5 {Anyway!} ({
The most popular reply is} 6... Bb4 7. e4 $140 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Qa5 9. e5 Ne4) ({
Notably, Botvinnik has used in the decisive last game of his first World
