seen} 10... Nd5 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. Rb1 Qa2 13. e4 Bd6 $13 {Radjabov -
Harikrishna, chess24.com INT, 2020}) 11. Rb1 Qa3 {and now:} 12. Nb5 {seems to
be the preference of the Armenian players -} (12. Ra1 Qb2 $11 (12... Qb3 13.
Qc1 O-O $11)) (12. Qc2 O-O 13. Ne5 (13. e3 Bxc3 14. Qxc3 Qxc3 15. Bxc3 Ba6 16.
Be2 Ne4 17. Rc1 Nxc3 18. Rxc3 Nd7 $11 {is anout equal, though White has to do
some work before restoring the material balance}) 13... Ba6 (13... Bxc3 14.
Qxc3 Qxc3 15. Bxc3 Nbd7 16. Nxc4 Ba6 $11) 14. e3 Rc8 15. Be2 Bxc3 16. Bxc3 Nd5
17. Kd2 f6 18. Nf3 Nd7 19. e4 Nxc3 20. Qxc3 Qd6 {Nearly the same situation as
in the line with 13.e3, but here Black is right to preserve the queens in the
