29. Ra5 Rf8 30. Rb2 Qf6 31. Bg4 Rb6 32. Re2 Bb7 33. Kh2 Bd5 {Black has
consolidated, with so many pawns up for him the rest is just a matter of time.}
34. Rxa7 Rb3 35. Qc2 c3 36. Ra2 Qxd4 {0-1 Annakov - Lunev, Sochi, 1997}) 12...
Bxd2+ 13. Qxd2 ({in case of} 13. Nxd2 Qe7 14. e3 O-O 15. Bxc4 {Sargissian -
