} 16. O-O (16. Qb4 Qxb4+ 17. Rxb4 a5 18. Rb2 Bxf3 (18... Nbd7 19. Ke2 Rfb8 $11)
19. gxf3 Rc8 20. Na3 {and here comes the already familiar manoeuvre} Nc6 21.
Ke2 Nb4 $11 {Melkumyan - Salem, Sitges, 2017}) 16... Bxf3 $5 (16... Nc6) 17.
gxf3 {and again} Nc6 18. Rfc1 a5 $11) 9... Bxa3 {Black should better keep the
c4-pawn rather than:} (9... Qxb2 $143 10. Nxc4 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 Bxd2+ 12. Ncxd2 $14
) (9... Ne4 {is aiming at exchanging Bg5, but after} 10. Nxc4 Qb4+ 11. Ncd2
Nxg5 12. Nxg5 Qxd4 13. e3 Qd7 14. Bc4 {Black is too behind in development -}
