17. Bxd3 Rxc1+ 18. Qxc1 Bxd3 19. Nd2 Nxd2 20. Kxd2 Qxb3 21. Qc3 (21. Qc6+ Kf7
22. Rc1 Re8 23. Rc3 Qb5 $11) 21... Qxc3+ 22. Kxc3 Bb5 $11 {and, as usual, the
presence of the opposite-coloured bishops has been a precondition for a draw,
