Ne4 ({Even though it does not contain a double threat,} 33... Nd3 {has the
right to exist. However, the textmove, which is aimed at eliminating the
blockading piece, makes more sense.}) 34. Nf3 ({White does not have the right
to activate voluntarily the enemy king by} 34. Nxe4 $6 Kxe4 $15 {[%csl Gd4,Ge4]
[%cal Ge4d3]}) 34... d3 35. Rd1 Kc4 36. Re1 (36. Kf1 a6 37. Re1 f5 $44) 36...
f5 37. Re3 (37. Ne5+ Kd4 38. Nf3+ Kc4 $11 {is just repeating.}) 37... Kb3 $1
38. Rxd3+ Kxb2 39. Rd8 (39. Nd4 {does not change the assessment of the endgame
as dynamically balanced, as demonstrated by} Nc5 40. Re3 f4 41. gxf4 (41. Rf3
fxg3 42. fxg3 Rd7 43. Rf4 Nd3 44. Re4 Nc5 $11) 41... Rxh4 42. Kg3 Rh1 43. f5
Rd1 44. Nc6 b3 $11) 39... b3 40. Nd4 Ka2 41. Nxb3 Kxb3 42. Rf8 Nd6 43. Rf6 Rd7
44. Kf3 Kb4 ({The position remains balanced in case of} 44... Kc4 45. Kf4 Kd5
$11 {due to the far advanced h-pawn after} 46. h5 Rc7 47. h6 $44 {/=}) 45. Kf4
Kxa5 46. h5 Kb5 47. h6 a5 {with full demolition of the board after} 48. h7 Rxh7
49. Rxd6 a4 $11 *

